## Initializing an Indexer

Now that you have installed the prerequisite packages required, letâ€™s jump into the practical steps of setting up the indexer for the Optimism Bridge on both networks using our no-code contract import feature. This feature allows users to quickly and easily start up an indexer with basic logic using an existing contract that has already been deployed on a blockchain.

1. Open your terminal in an empty repository and initialize a new indexer by running the command â€˜envio init.â€™ 


2. Name your indexer. In this example, we named our indexer â€œoptimism-bridge-indexerâ€ but feel free to name your indexer anything you prefer.


3. Choose a language, select contract import, and import from the block explorer. For this demonstration, weâ€™ve chosen to use TypeScript as the language. 

> Note: Indexers on Envio can be written in JavaScript, TypeScript, or ReScript.
 
4. Choose â€œBlock Explorerâ€ then select â€œOptimismâ€, insert the Optimism bridge contract address from OP Etherscan, and select the events you would like to index. In this case, weâ€™ll be indexing the "deposit finalized" event.  

To select an event navigate using the arrow keys (â†‘ â†“) and click the space bar once you have made your choice. 

Note: Multiple events can be selected and indexed at the same time. 

Optimism bridge contract address: 0x4200000000000000000000000000000000000010

5. Add another contract address, in this case, weâ€™ve imported from the block explorer just like before, added the Optimism Gateway smart contract address on Ethereum Mainnet from Etherscan, and opted to index the events "eth deposit initiated.â€ Finally, review the configuration and select â€œIâ€™m finishedâ€ to start generating the indexer.

